{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "In many poor and developing countries, thousands of mentally ill people are warehoused in dirty and dangerous institutions.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by writer John Rudolf contends that the asylum-based model of mental health care remains the standard across much of the globe, and that in many poor and developing countries thousands of mentally ill people are warehoused in dirty and dangerous institutions; highlights progress made in Guatemala to significantly reduce its long-term institutionalized population; calls for a global effort to expose abuses and shame governments into enacting serious reforms.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "5", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "John", "role": "reported", "lastname": "RUDOLF", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By JOHN RUDOLF", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/03/opinion/sunday/where-mental-asylums-live-on.html", "lead_paragraph": "In many poor and developing countries, thousands of mentally ill people are warehoused in dirty and dangerous institutions.", "headline": {"main": "Where Mental Asylums Live On", "print_headline": "Where Mental Asylums Live On", "content_kicker": "Opinion", "kicker": "Opinion"}, "_id": "5273f5c138f0d861d9d157b7", "word_count": "1107", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2013/11/03/opinion/03mental-img/03mental-img-thumbWide-v2.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2013/11/03/opinion/03mental-img/03mental-img-thumbWide-v2.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 448, "url": "images/2013/11/03/opinion/03mental-img/03mental-img-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2013/11/03/opinion/03mental-img/03mental-img-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "448"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2013/11/03/opinion/03mental-img/03me